# Power Efficiency

The [[61-Archive/20220223192844-power|power]] is most efficient when a [[61-Archive/20220221170305-battery|battery]]'s internal [[61-Archive/20220408115601-resistance|resistance]] is equal to the other resistances in the circuit. (See --> [[61-Archive/20220413104633-power-is-most-efficient-when-r-equals-r|Power is most efficient when r equals R]])

$P=I^2R$
